{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"compacted_at":1784257579144827980,"compiled_state":{"alias":"lovesick-crotchety-mouflon","assignee":"","author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","authorship":{"signed":5,"unsigned":0},"authorship_ledger":[{"content_hash":"9b24dd60d5a17562abd53c5ebaddcb045e902755c4800c685b1307bb02b3e8c3","event_uuid":"62b4f734-bb01-4fa7-808b-bb044e89f6f6","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784254251683093001-62b4f734-bb01-4fa7-808b-bb044e89f6f6"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"7415dbc84f417adb55a1ef054917a5f0212611d0122a49ce6c3ffefc549c1ec3","event_uuid":"2d989fc6-39bf-4f0b-a93f-6f8880b2b335","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784254254467556001-2d989fc6-39bf-4f0b-a93f-6f8880b2b335"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"8abd84e67b2c33c0d51d0a4d138fccdd4bbd902b352e04c2bef8d8f16dd3d5e0","event_uuid":"c99a1a9e-7397-418f-b28f-292be2bd4797","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784255800850488001-c99a1a9e-7397-418f-b28f-292be2bd4797"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"ae94329601b85b9cbfcef9fe118923bc641449349102639788737a70b28d5d39","event_uuid":"02b770ab-ad11-4850-85ad-01a8903c4a36","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784255801248952001-02b770ab-ad11-4850-85ad-01a8903c4a36"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"e59ce6a4c5441581bc3023d3c377c4881719e2bcf33f3304fcc79ced4d4cfa11","event_uuid":"a5014f45-1595-45b0-9e1f-ea3be880ba26","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784257579144827979-a5014f45-1595-45b0-9e1f-ea3be880ba26"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-212_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"5c2eef83-9ceb-4320-ad07-f54047bb7399","comments":[],"created_at":1784254251683093001,"deps":[{"link_uuid":"2d989fc6-39bf-4f0b-a93f-6f8880b2b335","relation":"discovered_from","target_id":"21dd-8681-4447-4bc0"}],"description":"## Summary\n\n`rebar criteria eval <project.criterion>` (and the underlying\n`calibrate_criterion`) cannot run the LIVE calibration of any project criterion\nwhose logical id contains the `project.` namespace dot, because the physical\nprompt-id → criterion-id round-trip is lossy.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n\n1. Activate a project criterion via `.rebar/criteria_routing.json` (e.g.\n   `project.portability`, `exec: 1-TURN`) with a rubric prompt and an eval fixture\n   at `.rebar/evals/plan-review-project-portability.eval.yaml`.\n2. Run `rebar criteria eval project.portability --runs 1 --output json`.\n\nExpected: the criterion runs live over the dataset and prints calibration metrics.\n\nActual: exits non-zero with\n`ValueError: no eval solver for prompt 'plan-review-project-portability'`\nfrom `eval_solver.run_case`.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`rebar.llm.evals.eval.calibrate_criterion` computes\n`prompt_id = criterion_prompt_id(\"project.portability\")` = `plan-review-project-portability`\n(the forward map replaces `.`→`-`) to load the eval fixture (correct). But the default\n`_criterion_solver.solve(prompt_id, case)` passes that DASH prompt-id to\n`eval_solver.run_case`, which resolves the criterion via `_criterion_id(prompt_id)`:\nit strips the `plan-review-` prefix to `project-portability` (dash) and checks\n`cid in registry.by_id(repo_root)`. The registry is keyed by the LOGICAL id\n`project.portability` (dot), so the dash form is never found → `_criterion_id` returns\nNone → `run_case` raises `no eval solver`. Built-in ids (no dot) round-trip fine; only\nnamespaced `project.<name>` criteria break. Confirmed:\n`_criterion_id(\"plan-review-project-portability\", root)` → None, while\n`_criterion_id(\"project.portability\", root)` → \"project.portability\".\n\n## Proposed Fix (one of)\n\n- `_criterion_solver` / `calibrate_criterion`: resolve the criterion in `run_case` from\n  the ORIGINAL logical `criterion_id` (dot), using the dash `prompt_id` only for\n  `load_eval_spec`; or\n- `eval_solver._criterion_id`: after stripping `plan-review-`, also try mapping a leading\n  `project-<name>` back to `project.<name>` (the namespaced project-criterion inverse),\n  since `<name>` has no dots.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `rebar criteria eval <project.criterion>` resolves and runs the project criterion's\n      Pass-1 finder over its dataset (no `no eval solver` error), for a criterion whose\n      logical id contains the `project.` namespace dot.\n- [ ] A regression test drives `calibrate_criterion` (or `eval_solver.run_case`) for an\n      activated `project.<name>` criterion with an injected/fake runner and asserts the\n      criterion resolves (fires/does-not-fire per the fake), proving the physical→logical\n      round-trip. File: `tests/unit/test_criteria_eval.py` (or a sibling).\n- [ ] Built-in criterion calibration (e.g. `F1`) is unchanged (no regression).","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[],"parent_id":null,"parent_status_uuid":"c99a1a9e-7397-418f-b28f-292be2bd4797","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"2340-1b72-109a-43d7","ticket_type":"bug","title":"Live criteria-eval cannot resolve namespaced project criteria (dash/dot round-trip)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["62b4f734-bb01-4fa7-808b-bb044e89f6f6","2d989fc6-39bf-4f0b-a93f-6f8880b2b335","c99a1a9e-7397-418f-b28f-292be2bd4797","02b770ab-ad11-4850-85ad-01a8903c4a36","a5014f45-1595-45b0-9e1f-ea3be880ba26"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784257579144827980,"uuid":"115e1f2b-33dd-4556-b4c9-f9d349a12274"}